# Axonary — governance & publishing

**Registry and SEO mechanics:** `seo-rules.mdc`  
**Voice and copy patterns:** `content-rules.mdc`  
**Process:** `workflow.mdc`

---

## Publishing standards

- No page ships without passing the **SEO QA checklist** below (when the page is indexable and intended to rank).  
- Legal/utility pages may skip SEO items unless intentionally indexed.  
- Human review for factual claims, compliance, and brand alignment before production deploy.

---

## SEO QA checklist (mandatory gate)

Block publish until applicable items pass:

- [ ] **Intent** — single TOFU/MOFU/BOFU; matches `seo-rules.mdc` registry or approved brief.  
- [ ] **Keywords** — primary in **H1**, **first ~100 words**, reflected in **H2s** (no stuffing).  
- [ ] **Internal links** — **3–5** contextual links; intentional anchor mix per `seo-rules.mdc`.  
- [ ] **External authority** — **1** link to a recognized authoritative source.  
- [ ] **Entities** — **15+** named entities listed (target 15–25).  
- [ ] **Readability** — ~US grades **6–8**; short sentences; jargon defined.  
- [ ] **CTA** — visible **above** and **below** fold (or end of main content on mobile).  
- [ ] **No stuffing** — natural language.

---

## Per-page delivery checklist (operational)

**Pre-flight**

- [ ] URL confirmed; intent + primary from `seo-rules.mdc` registry (or approved brief).  
- [ ] One business goal + one conversion path documented.

**Structure & keywords**

- [ ] H1 = exact-match primary.  
- [ ] H2 coverage: Problem, Solution, Features, Benefits, Use Cases, CTA.  
- [ ] Word count: service 800–1200 / blog 1200–1800.

**Semantics & links**

- [ ] 15+ entities; CRM semantics on CRM/sales pages where relevant.  
- [ ] 3–5 internal + 1 external authority.

**Meta**

- [ ] Title 55–60 chars; description 140–155 chars.

**Iteration**

- [ ] Gaps fixed; re-check until all pass.  
- [ ] Log publish in **content update loop** below.

---

## CRO + experimentation

- **A/B:** headlines (H1/hero), primary CTAs.  
- **Window:** **14–28 days** before calling a winner.  
- **Metrics:** CTR (snippet + on-page), conversion rate (GA4).  
- Document hypothesis, variant, outcome in the update log.

---

## Content performance tracking (per URL)

GSC + GA4 (or agreed stack): organic clicks, impressions, CTR, rankings, conversion rate, bounce/engagement rate, engagement time.

---

## Content update loop

Log every material change:

| Field | Example |
|-------|---------|
| Date | ISO date |
| URL | Path |
| Change type | Refresh, H1, meta, schema, links |
| Target keyword | Primary |
| Expected impact | Rank, CTR, conversions |
| Owner | Name |

**Re-evaluate** after **28 days**; record results in the same log.
